You now have 3 options, from easiest to most automatic:

🖱️ Option 1 — Desktop Shortcuts (Just Created!)
Two

.desktop
 launchers are now on your Desktop:

Nordseye Server — double-click to start in a terminal window
Nordseye Agent — double-click to start the overlay (you may need to right-click → "Allow Launching" once in Ubuntu)

⚠️ Update the --server IP in the Agent shortcut if the server is on a different machine. Right-click the

.desktop
 file → Open with Text Editor.


 💻 Option 2 — Terminal Commands (Quick & Reliable)
Server (on the server machine):
cd ~/Documents/nordseye/nordseye-networked/server
python3 server.py


Agent (on each client PC — change the IP!):
cd ~/Documents/nordseye/nordseye-networked/client
python3 agent.py --server 192.168.1.100 --name "PC 01"


Then open the web admin dashboard in a browser:
http://localhost:8766          # on the server machine
http://192.168.1.100:8766      # from any PC on the network


⚙️ Option 3 — systemd Auto-Start on Boot (Most Permanent)
Run once on each machine. It will auto-start on every boot and restart itself if it crashes:
# On the SERVER machine:
cd ~/Documents/nordseye/nordseye-networked/server
sudo ./install-server.sh

# On each CLIENT PC:
cd ~/Documents/nordseye/nordseye-networked/client
SERVER_IP=192.168.1.100 PC_NAME="PC 01" sudo ./install-client.sh


After that, manage with:
systemctl status nordseye-server    # check server status
systemctl status nordseye-agent     # check agent status
journalctl -u nordseye-server -f    # live server logs
journalctl -u nordseye-agent -f     # live agent logs


